Looking at line 367-375:
```rust
pub fn mark_run_completed_with_error(msg: &str) {
    store_run_error(msg);
    let error_detail = take_diagnostic_error();
    record(
        EventType::RunCompleted,
        Actor::Harness,
        run_completed_payload("error", Some(msg), error_detail.as_deref()),
    );
}
```

And `exit_with_state` at line 971-978:
```rust
fn exit_with_state(code: i32) -> ! {
    let status = if code == 0 { "completed" } else { "error" };
    if code != 0 {
        state::mark_run_completed_with_error(&format!("exit code {}", code));
    } else {
        state::mark_run_completed(status);
    }
    std::process::exit(code);
}
```

So when exit_with_state(1) is called:
1. It calls mark_run_completed_with_error("exit code 1")
2. mark_run_completed_with_error calls take_diagnostic_error() to get the stashed error
3. The error_detail is included in the RunCompleted payload

